WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.600
[Birds chirping]
[鸟鸣声]

00:00:02.600 --> 00:00:05.200
What does that mean, "You want more"?
你说“你想要更多”是什么意思？

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:06.700
Am I not enough, or...?
是我不够好吗，还是……？

00:00:06.700 --> 00:00:09.300
You are. You know you are.
你很好。你知道的。

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:11.300
It's not what I meant.
我不是那个意思。

00:00:11.300 --> 00:00:14.500
[Footsteps]
[脚步声]

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:16.400
So what did you mean, then?
那你是什么意思？

00:00:16.400 --> 00:00:20.200
Just... that it's time for a change.
只是……是时候做出改变了。

00:00:20.200 --> 00:00:22.000
So you don't believe in us, in this?
所以你不相信我们，不相信这段感情？

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:23.900
Just forget I said anything.
就当我说错话了吧。

00:00:23.900 --> 00:00:27.100
My timing's always been terrible, even my mom says so.
我总是选错时机，连我妈都这么说。

00:00:27.100 --> 00:00:30.400
'Cause you were born in the back of a taxicab during a snowstorm.
因为你是在暴风雪中出生在出租车后座的。

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:33.400
[Birds chirping]
[鸟鸣声]

00:00:33.400 --> 00:00:38.200
[Footsteps]
[脚步声]

00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:39.600
I have faith.
我有信心。

00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:41.500
Let it be enough for both of us.
让我们彼此都知足吧。

00:00:41.500 --> 00:00:42.800
Let's go.
我们走吧。

00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:45.800
[Footsteps]
[脚步声]

00:00:45.800 --> 00:00:48.800
[Footsteps]
[脚步声]

00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:51.800
[Footsteps]
[脚步声]

00:00:51.800 --> 00:00:54.800
[Footsteps]
[脚步声]

00:00:54.800 --> 00:00:59.800
[Indistinct chatter]
[模糊的谈话声]

00:00:59.800 --> 00:01:01.600
Love you.
我爱你。

00:01:01.600 --> 00:01:03.400
Love you, too.
我也爱你。

00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:06.400
[Footsteps]
[脚步声]

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:10.000
[Birds chirping]
[鸟鸣声]

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:16.400
I ask you, what is more important, art or our planet?
我问你，什么更重要，艺术还是我们的星球？

00:01:16.400 --> 00:01:18.000
[Gunfire]
[枪声]

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:19.600
Security! Security to mezzanine!
保安！保安到中层来！

00:01:19.600 --> 00:01:20.600
We are killing our planet!
我们正在毁灭我们的星球！

00:01:20.600 --> 00:01:21.600
We've got a defacement of progress!
我們的進展被破壞了！

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:24.700
The temperature of the Earth is increasing day by day!
地球的溫度每天都在上升！

00:01:24.700 --> 00:01:27.400
Great day!
美好的一天！

00:01:27.400 --> 00:01:28.400
Put your hands in the air!
把你的手舉起來！

00:01:28.400 --> 00:01:29.400
Oh, hey, hey, hey!
哦，嘿，嘿，嘿！

00:01:29.400 --> 00:01:30.400
Turn around. Let me see your hands.
轉過身來。讓我看看你的手。

00:01:30.400 --> 00:01:31.400
Let me see your hands.
讓我看看你的手。

00:01:31.400 --> 00:01:32.400
Hey, stop!
嘿，停下來！

00:01:32.400 --> 00:01:33.400
Turn around.
轉過身來。

00:01:33.400 --> 00:01:34.400
Let me see your hands.
讓我看看你的手。

00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:36.400
[Grunting]
[咕噥聲]

00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:37.400
Stop it, girl.
停下來，女孩。

00:01:37.400 --> 00:01:38.400
[Gunshot]
[槍聲]

00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:41.400
[Screaming]
[尖叫聲]

00:01:41.400 --> 00:01:42.400
[Gasps]
[喘息聲]

00:01:42.400 --> 00:01:44.400
[Gasps]
[倒抽一口氣]

00:01:44.400 --> 00:01:45.400
Donna!
唐娜！

00:01:45.400 --> 00:01:46.400
Let's go!
我們走吧！

00:01:46.400 --> 00:01:47.400
[Gasps]
[倒抽一口氣]

00:01:47.400 --> 00:01:48.400
[Gasps]
[倒抽一口氣]

00:01:48.400 --> 00:01:49.400
[Gasps]
[倒抽一口氣]

00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:50.400
[Screaming]
[尖叫]

00:01:50.400 --> 00:02:05.400
[Music]
[音樂]

00:02:05.400 --> 00:02:07.400
Hey, what happened to my thumb?
嘿，我的拇指怎麼了？

00:02:07.400 --> 00:02:08.400
[Horn honks]
[喇叭聲]

00:02:08.400 --> 00:02:11.400
[Laughs]
[笑聲]

00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:13.400
Dad, don't do that.
爸，別這樣。

00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:15.400
You're gonna get him all riled up right before his nap.
你在他午睡前這樣會讓他興奮起來的。

00:02:15.400 --> 00:02:16.400
A nap?
午睡？

00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:17.400
We haven't even been eating yet.
我們還沒開始吃呢。

00:02:17.400 --> 00:02:19.400
Stuart's getting the food right now.
史都華現在去拿食物了。

00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:20.400
Right away?
馬上嗎？

00:02:20.400 --> 00:02:23.400
You and your sister used to love when I played this game.
你和你姐姐以前很喜歡我玩這個遊戲。

00:02:23.400 --> 00:02:28.400
Your mom would get so mad at me when I would play it just before bedtime.
每當我在睡覺前玩這個遊戲時，你媽媽都會對我生氣。

00:02:28.400 --> 00:02:30.400
He does the same to my kids right before bedtime.
他現在也在我孩子睡覺前這樣做。

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:31.400
Of course he does.
當然他會這樣。

00:02:31.400 --> 00:02:34.400
Yes, I'm gonna get his milk.
是的，我要去拿他的牛奶。

00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:39.400
You know, Marina, your niece and nephew sure would like to get to know you better.
你知道嗎，瑪麗娜，你的姪子和姪女肯定會想更了解你。

00:02:39.400 --> 00:02:41.400
Yes, I know, Dad.
是的，我知道，爸爸。

00:02:41.400 --> 00:02:44.400
And I will make my way to Houston just as soon as I can.
我會盡快前往休士頓。

00:02:44.400 --> 00:02:46.400
Well, we decided if you all wouldn't come to Houston,
嗯，我們決定如果你們不來休士頓，

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:48.400
then Houston would come to New York.
那麼休士頓就會來紐約。

00:02:48.400 --> 00:02:51.400
Although why anyone would live in this city is beyond me.
雖然我不明白為什麼有人會住在這個城市。

00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:56.400
The noise, the crazies, and the streets are dirtier than a herd of hogs.
噪音、瘋子和街道比一群豬還髒。

00:02:56.400 --> 00:02:58.400
Okay, time to eat.
好了，該吃飯了。

00:02:58.400 --> 00:03:00.400
Oh, sorry.
哦，抱歉。

00:03:00.400 --> 00:03:01.400
Okay, burritos are here.
好的，墨西哥卷饼到了。

00:03:01.400 --> 00:03:02.400
Burritos.
墨西哥卷饼。

00:03:02.400 --> 00:03:05.400
Oh, and a turkey sandwich for Mr. Chase.
哦，还有给蔡斯先生的火鸡三明治。

00:03:05.400 --> 00:03:06.400
Well, let me pay for those.
让我来付这些吧。

00:03:06.400 --> 00:03:08.400
Oh, no, I took care of it.
哦，不用了，我已经付了。

00:03:08.400 --> 00:03:12.400
Marina, your sister and I did not drive three days so that you would have to pay for our meals.
玛丽娜，你姐姐和我开了三天的车，不是为了让你付我们的餐费的。

00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:14.400
You didn't have to drive, you know that, right?
你们其实不用开车的，你知道的吧？

00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:17.400
There's a direct flight, Houston to New York, it's three hours.
有直达航班，从休斯顿到纽约，只要三个小时。

00:03:17.400 --> 00:03:20.400
Well, Daddy likes to drive so he can smoke.
嗯，爸爸喜欢开车，这样他可以抽烟。

00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:22.400
I'm well aware.
我很清楚。

00:03:22.400 --> 00:03:26.400
You know, I'm just still impressed that you guys were able to find parking on the block.
你知道吗，我还是很惊讶你们能在街区找到停车位。

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:28.400
Here, I insist.
来，我一定要付。

00:03:28.400 --> 00:03:29.400
Oh, okay.
哦，好吧。

00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:31.400
Yeah, I'll get dinner.
对，晚餐我来付。

00:03:31.400 --> 00:03:34.400
There's a great Japanese place just opened up down the street.
街尾新開了一家很棒的日本餐廳。

00:03:34.400 --> 00:03:35.400
I know the owners.
我認識老闆。

00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:39.400
Sorry, you guys are going to have to go visit the Empire State Building without me.
抱歉，你們得自己去參觀帝國大廈了。

00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:42.400
There was a shooting at the Queens Museum, so I've got to get moving now.
皇后區博物館發生了槍擊案，所以我得趕快過去。

00:03:42.400 --> 00:03:44.400
Well, Marina, don't worry about us.
瑪麗娜，別擔心我們。

00:03:44.400 --> 00:03:49.400
Daddy, why? Why do you insist on calling me Marina when you know my name is Nina?
爸爸，為什麼？你明明知道我叫妮娜，為什麼堅持叫我瑪麗娜？

00:03:49.400 --> 00:03:51.400
Well, you were my Marina when you left.
你離開時還是我的瑪麗娜啊。

00:03:51.400 --> 00:03:52.400
Daddy!
爸爸！

00:03:52.400 --> 00:03:54.400
All right, Marina, I got it.
好吧，瑪麗娜，我知道了。

00:03:54.400 --> 00:03:56.400
Nina, you see, I can change.
妮娜，你看，我會改變的。

00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:58.400
It's very impressive.
這很令人印象深刻。

00:03:58.400 --> 00:04:00.400
Okay, we got this.
好了，我們可以的。

00:04:00.400 --> 00:04:01.400
You sure?
你確定？

00:04:01.400 --> 00:04:02.400
It's going to be great. Come on.
會很棒的。來吧。

00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:04.400
Culture, sightseeing, I love you.
文化、觀光，我愛你。

00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:06.400
Sorry.
抱歉。

00:04:06.400 --> 00:04:07.400
I love you.
我爱你。

00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:07.400
I love you too, thank you.
我也爱你，谢谢。

00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:09.400
Join us for dinner.
和我们一起吃晚餐吧。

00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:11.400
I will try.
我会试试。

00:04:11.400 --> 00:04:16.400
[music]
[音乐]

00:04:16.400 --> 00:04:18.400
I just got off the phone with Isabel.
我刚和伊莎贝尔通完电话。

00:04:18.400 --> 00:04:21.400
The mayor himself reached out asking for our help finding these two shooters.
市长亲自联系，要求我们帮忙找到这两名枪手。

00:04:21.400 --> 00:04:28.400
We need to reassure the public they can go to a museum and not end up covered in pig blood like some reenactment of Carrie.
我们需要向公众保证，他们可以去博物馆，而不会像《魔女嘉莉》的重现那样被猪血覆盖。

00:04:28.400 --> 00:04:29.400
What do we know so far?
我们目前知道什么？

00:04:29.400 --> 00:04:33.400
All right, so we got Emma Culp, Trevor Allen, both 28, both from New York.
好的，我们有艾玛·卡尔普和特雷弗·艾伦，两人都是28岁，来自纽约。

00:04:33.400 --> 00:04:38.400
They're climate change activists who belong to a group called Global Climate Fund.
他们是气候变化活动家，属于一个名为“全球气候基金”的组织。

00:04:38.400 --> 00:04:41.400
There are no strangers to public acts of defiance.
他们对公开的挑衅行为并不陌生。

00:04:41.400 --> 00:04:44.400
Are they the ones that disrupted the performance of enemy of the people?
他们是那些干扰《人民公敌》演出的人吗？

00:04:44.400 --> 00:04:48.400
Yes, they were also involved with the campus protests at Ridgewell College three weeks ago.
是的，他们还参与了三周前里奇韦尔学院的校园抗议活动。

00:04:48.400 --> 00:04:52.400
So maybe the assault is a reaction, a payback for the shooting.
所以也許這次襲擊是一種反應，是對槍擊事件的報復。

00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:56.400
A cell phone footage didn't catch them saying anything about retribution before the guard was shot.
手機錄影沒有捕捉到他們在守衛被射擊前提到任何關於報復的事情。

00:04:56.400 --> 00:04:58.400
Maybe they didn't mean to shoot him.
也許他們並不是故意射擊他。

00:04:58.400 --> 00:05:00.400
Yeah, they didn't take a weapon into the museum.
是的，他們沒有帶武器進入博物館。

00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:02.400
Trevor also didn't leave the gun behind.
特雷弗也沒有留下槍。

00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:06.400
Could be a sense of fatalism kicked in after the shooting like they have nothing left to lose.
可能是在槍擊後有種宿命感襲來，就像他們已經沒有什麼可失去的了。

00:05:06.400 --> 00:05:08.400
We should be ready for anything with these two.
我們應該對這兩個人做好一切準備。

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:11.400
So they went into Corona Park. Any eyes on them since?
所以他們進入了科羅納公園。之後有看到他們嗎？

00:05:11.400 --> 00:05:14.400
Uh, let's see.
嗯，讓我看看。

00:05:14.400 --> 00:05:19.400
No, all the cameras in the park are down due to a recent update. Everything's offline.
沒有，公園裡的所有攝像頭因為最近的更新都關閉了。一切都離線了。

00:05:19.400 --> 00:05:21.400
Their phones are off also.
他們的手機也關機了。

00:05:21.400 --> 00:05:24.400
Are these two together? Trevor and Emma?
這兩個人在一起嗎？特雷弗和艾瑪？

00:05:24.400 --> 00:05:27.400
Maybe. I went through Emma's social media.
可能吧。我查看了艾瑪的社交媒體。

00:05:27.400 --> 00:05:32.400
She was at Pride in June. She stands for "Love is Love."
她六月份參加了驕傲遊行。她支持「愛就是愛」。

00:05:32.400 --> 00:05:35.400
Clearly she's never been divorced. Love is expensive.
顯然她從未離過婚。愛是昂貴的。

00:05:35.400 --> 00:05:38.400
I mean, she might have a girlfriend too.
我是说，她可能也有个女朋友。

00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:40.400
Hmm. I wonder if she's loyal to Trevor.
嗯。我在想她是否对特雷弗忠诚。

00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:42.400
One might flip on the other.
一方可能会背叛另一方。

00:05:42.400 --> 00:05:45.400
Hannah, does this Global Climate Front have an office or anything?
汉娜，这个全球气候前线有办公室之类的吗？

00:05:45.400 --> 00:05:51.400
Yes. I tracked their headquarters to Brooklyn, not far from Emma's apartment.
是的。我追踪到他们的总部在布鲁克林，离艾玛的公寓不远。

00:05:51.400 --> 00:05:54.400
New Cycle's doing a hell of a job of boloing these two.
新周期在追踪这两个人方面做得非常出色。

00:05:54.400 --> 00:05:58.400
You and I will go to their headquarters. Nina Ray, check on Emma's digs.
你和我去他们的总部。妮娜·雷，你去查查艾玛的住处。

00:05:58.400 --> 00:05:59.400
They're on their way.
他们已经在路上了。

00:05:59.400 --> 00:06:01.400
Hey, what's the latest with Barnes?
嘿，巴恩斯那边有什么最新消息吗？

00:06:01.400 --> 00:06:02.400
She says she's back next week for sure.
她说她下周肯定回来。

00:06:02.400 --> 00:06:04.400
Okay. See you in the car.
好的。车里见。

00:06:04.400 --> 00:06:06.400
Okay.
好的。

00:06:06.400 --> 00:06:11.400
So I saw Emma leave this morning with that guy on the news.
我今天早上看到艾玛和新闻上的那个男人一起离开了。

00:06:11.400 --> 00:06:14.400
Thought maybe he spent the night. They went for a breakfast.
以为他可能在她那儿过夜了。他们一起去吃了早餐。

00:06:14.400 --> 00:06:20.400
Okay. Do we have a sense of the people in her life? Maybe who she's dating?
好的。我们对她的生活中的人有了解吗？也许她在和谁约会？

00:06:20.400 --> 00:06:25.400
Everything's so fluid these days, right? Girls with girls, girls with guys, girls with girls and guys.
現在一切都這麼流動，對吧？女孩和女孩在一起，女孩和男孩在一起，女孩和女孩和男孩在一起。

00:06:25.400 --> 00:06:26.400
So that's a no.
所以這是不行。

00:06:26.400 --> 00:06:30.400
Well, the Trevor guy's the only person I've seen around here on the regular.
嗯，特雷弗是我在這裡經常見到的唯一一個人。

00:06:30.400 --> 00:06:32.400
Her fridge is full.
她的冰箱是滿的。

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:34.400
Yeah, these are two and she has a suitcase in there.
是的，這裡有兩個，她還有一個行李箱在那裡。

00:06:34.400 --> 00:06:36.400
It doesn't look like she was going on the run that day.
看起來她那天並沒有打算逃跑。

00:06:36.400 --> 00:06:39.400
Well, they're definitely improvising and don't have a plan.
嗯，他們肯定是在即興發揮，沒有計劃。

00:06:39.400 --> 00:06:42.400
Do we know what Emma did for employment?
我們知道艾瑪做什麼工作嗎？

00:06:42.400 --> 00:06:46.400
Internships mostly. Her and Trevor have a spotty employment record.
主要是實習。她和特雷弗的工作記錄都不太穩定。

00:06:46.400 --> 00:06:49.400
Do you know if a trust fund pays the rent for this place?
你知道這個地方的租金是由信託基金支付的嗎？

00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:53.400
So now get this. On the news, they say they're looking for an Emma Cope.
所以現在聽好了。新聞上說他們在找一個叫艾瑪·科普的人。

00:06:53.400 --> 00:06:56.400
But her rent checks always come from a Jefferies Corp.
但她的租金支票總是來自傑弗里斯公司。

00:06:56.400 --> 00:06:58.400
Jefferies Corporation.
傑弗里斯公司。

00:06:58.400 --> 00:07:00.400
Yeah.
是的。

00:07:02.400 --> 00:07:07.400
All right, so there's a Jefferies family. They made most of the money in oil.
好吧，所以有一個傑弗里斯家族。他們的大部分錢都是從石油中賺來的。

00:07:07.400 --> 00:07:11.400
Emma's father, Alexander Cope Jefferies, died two years ago.
艾瑪的父親，亞歷山大·科普·傑弗里斯，兩年前去世了。

00:07:11.400 --> 00:07:16.400
Okay, so her climate activist fugitive comes from oil money.
好吧，所以她這個氣候活動家的逃犯來自石油財富。

00:07:16.400 --> 00:07:21.400
Maybe she's trying to repay some common debt, use her inheritance to raise awareness for climate change.
